ingredients: ["3 lb. shrimp in shell", "2 large onions, chopped fine", "3 ribs celery, chopped fine", "3/4 c. butter or oil (or more)", "1 bell pepper, chopped fine", "garlic powder to taste", "black pepper to taste", "red pepper to taste"]
directions: ["Season shrimp in shell with salt, black pepper, red pepper and garlic powder.", "Put shrimp in hot oil or butter and stir until all shrimp turn pink.", "Add onions, celery and bell pepper.", "Mix well; cook, covered, for 15 minutes.", "When done, using slotted spoon, move shrimp to platter.", "Serve juice in small bowls.", "When eating, suck on shrimp first, then peel shrimp.", "Can be dipped in juice or dip juice with French bread.", "Serve with green salad.", "Delicious! If real hungry, double recipe."]

title: Raised Cornmeal Muffins
ingredients: ["1 pkg. yeast", "1/4 c. lukewarm water", "1 c. cornmeal", "2 c. scalded milk", "1 tsp. salt", "1/2 c. sugar", "1/2 c. shortening", "2 beaten eggs", "4 to 4 1/2 c. flour"]
directions: ["Soften yeast in water; pour milk over cornmeal, salt, sugar and shortening.", "Cool.", "Beat in eggs and 2 cups flour.", "Add yeast and mix well.", "Stir in flour.", "Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.", "Stir down; spoon into greased muffin cups.", "Fill about 1/3 full.", "Cover and let rise until double in bulk.", "Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400\u00b0.", "Brush with melted butter.", "Makes about 2 dozen."]

title: Chocolate Clair Cake
ingredients: ["1 c. flour", "1 stick butter or margarine", "1/4 tsp. salt", "1 c. water", "4 eggs (room temperature)", "2 (3.4 oz.) pkg. instant French vanilla pudding", "2 1/2 c. cold milk", "1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese, softened", "12 oz. Cool Whip", "3 oz. chocolate chips", "2 Tbsp. butter or margarine", "1 c. confectioners sugar", "3 to 4 Tbsp. milk"]
directions: ["In saucepan, bring water and butter to the boil until all butter is melted.", "All at once, add flour and salt; beat until mixture forms a ball that leaves the sides of the saucepan.", "Cool slightly.", "Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.", "Spread pastry mixture onto an ungreased jellyroll pan or cookie sheet.", "Bake in 400\u00b0 oven for 35 minutes.", "Remove from oven; pierce bubbles with fork while hot.", "Cool completely."]

title: Lemonade Pie
ingredients: ["1 can sweetened condensed milk", "1 small can frozen lemonade", "1 small container prepared whipped topping (Cool Whip)", "1 graham cracker crust"]
directions: ["Mix all ingredients until smooth.", "Pour in graham cracker crust. Chill several hours."]

title: Old-Fashioned Sweet Potatoes
ingredients: ["4 large sweet potatoes, cooked, peeled and sliced or 1 lb. can sweet potatoes, drained and sliced", "2 c. sugar", "3 c. water", "1 Tbsp. vanilla", "pinch of nutmeg", "1/2 Tbsp. lemon juice", "1 Tbsp. butter"]
directions: ["Lay out sweet potato slices in a buttered baking dish or pan. Mix remaining ingredients, except butter, and pour over potatoes. Dot with butter.", "Place in oven and bake for 35 minutes at 350\u00b0."]
